ussian football]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesr/rus04.html RSSSF]\n\n{{Russian Premier League seasons}}\n{{Football in Russia}}\n{{2003\u201304 in European football (UEFA)}}\n{{2004\u201305 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n[[Category:Russian Premier League seasons|2004]]\n[[Category:2004 in Russian football leagues|1]]\n[[Category:2003\u201304 in European association football leagues|Russia]]\n[[Category:2004\u201305 in European association football leagues|Russia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Russian Premier League]]\n| season             = 2004\n| winners            = [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]]\n| relegated          = [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]] <br> [[FC Rotor Volgograd|Rotor Volgograd]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[2005\u201306 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]] <br> [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[2005\u201306 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[PFC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov]] <br> [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit St.Petersburg]]\n| matches            = 240\n| total goals        = 598\n| league topscorer   = [[Aleksandr Kerzhakov]] (18)\n<!--\nNOTE: The following parameters require sources when filled out.\n-->\n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| longest wins       = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[2003 Russian Premier League|2003]]\n| nextseason         = [[2005 Russian Premier League|2005]]\n}}\n\nFollowing are the results of the '''2004 Russian Premier League''', the top division of Russian [[association football]].  Lokomotiv won their second [[Russian Premier League|Premier League]] title, while Krylya Sovetov finished in the top three for the first time, winning bronze. Kuban were relegated after just one season in the Premier League. They were joined by Rotor who played at the top level since the beginning of the Russian league.\n\n==Overview==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Team\n! Head coach\n|-\n| [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]]\n| [[Yuri Syomin]]\n|-\n| [[PFC CSKA Moscow]]\n| [[Artur Jorge (footballer)|Artur Jorge]] {{flagicon|POR}} (until July)<br />[[Valery Gazzaev]] (from July)\n|-\n| [[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara]]\n| [[Gadzhi Gadzhiyev]]\n|-\n| [[FC Zenit St. Petersburg]]\n| [[Vlastimil Petr\u017eela]] {{flagicon|CZE}}\n|-\n| [[FC Torpedo Moscow]]\n| [[Sergei Petrenko (footballer)|Sergei Petrenko]]\n|-\n| [[FC Shinnik Yaroslavl]]\n| [[Aleksandr Pobegalov]] (until May)<br />[[Valeri Frolov (footballer, born 1949)|Valeri Frolov]] (caretaker) (May)<br />[[Oleg Dolmatov]] (from May)\n|-\n| [[FC Saturn Ramenskoye]]\n| [[Boris Ignatyev]] (until September)<br />[[Alexander Tarkhanov]] (from September)\n|-\n| [[FC Spartak Moscow]]\n| [[Nevio Scala]] {{flagicon|ITA}} (until August)<br />[[Aleksandrs Starkovs]] {{flagicon|LVA}} (from September)\n|-\n| [[FC Moscow]]\n| [[Valeriy Petrakov]]\n|-\n| [[FC Rubin Kazan]]\n| [[Kurban Berdyev]] {{flagicon|TKM}}\n|-\n| [[FC Amkar Perm]]\n| [[Sergei Oborin]]\n|-\n| [[FC Rostov]]\n| [[Vitaliy Shevchenko]] (until April)<br />[[Sergei Balakhnin]] (from April)\n|-\n| [[FC Dynamo Moscow]]\n| [[Jaroslav H\u0159eb\u00edk]] {{flagicon|CZE}} (until July)<br />[[Viktor Bondarenko (football manager)|Viktor Bondarenko]] (caretaker) (July to October)<br />[[Oleg Romantsev]] (from October)\n|-\n| [[FC Spartak Vladikavkaz]]\n| [[Rolland Courbis]] {{flagicon|FRA}} (until September)<br />[[Dragan Cvetkovi\u0107]] {{flagicon|SRB}} (caretaker) (September to October)<br />[[Yuri Sekinayev]] (caretaker) (from October)\n|-\n| [[FC Kuban Krasnodar]]\n| [[Nikolai Yuzhanin]] (until May)<br />[[Soferbi Yeshugov]] (May to October)<br />[[Leonid Nazarenko]] (caretaker) (from October)\n|-\n| [[FC Rotor Volgograd]]\n| [[Vladimir Faizulin]] (until April)<br />[[Yuri Marushkin]] (caretaker) (April)<br />[[Valeriy Yaremchenko]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (April to June)<br />[[Yuri Marushkin]] (caretaker) (June to July)<br />[[Vladimir Faizulin]] (from July)\n|-\n|}\n\n==Standings==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|show_limit=5\n\n|team1=LOK|name_LOK=[[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]]\n|team2=CSK|name_CSK=[[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n|team3=KRY|name_KRY=[[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov Samara]]\n|team4=ZEN|name_ZEN=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit St. Petersburg]]\n|team5=TOR|name_TOR=[[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]]\n|team6=SHI|name_SHI=[[FC Shinnik Yaroslavl|Shinnik Yaroslavl]]\n|team7=SAT|name_SAT=[[FC Saturn Moscow Oblast (1946-2011)|Saturn]]\n|team8=SPA|name_SPA=[[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]]\n|team9=MOS|name_MOS=[[FC Moscow]]\n|team10=RUB|name_RUB=[[FC Rubin Kazan|Rubin Kazan]]\n|team11=AMK|name_AMK=[[FC Amkar Perm|Amkar Perm]]\n|team12=ROS|name_ROS=[[FC Rostov|Rostov]]\n|team13=DYN|name_DYN=[[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]\n|team14=ALA|name_ALA=[[FC Alania Vladikavkaz|Alania Vladikavkaz]]\n|team15=KUB|name_KUB=[[FC Kuban Krasnodar|Kuban Krasnodar]]\n|team16=ROT|name_ROT=[[FC Rotor Volgograd|Rotor Volgograd]]\n|win_LOK=18|draw_LOK=7|loss_LOK=5|gf_LOK=44|ga_LOK=19|status_LOK=C\n|win_CSK=17|draw_CSK=9|loss_CSK=4|gf_CSK=53|ga_CSK=22\n|win_KRY=17|draw_KRY=5|loss_KRY=8|gf_KRY=50|ga_KRY=41\n|win_ZEN=17|draw_ZEN=5|loss_ZEN=8|gf_ZEN=55|ga_ZEN=37\n|win_TOR=16|draw_TOR=6|loss_TOR=8|gf_TOR=53|ga_TOR=37\n|win_SHI=12|draw_SHI=8|loss_SHI=10|gf_SHI=29|ga_SHI=29\n|win_SAT=10|draw_SAT=11|loss_SAT=9|gf_SAT=37|ga_SAT=30\n|win_SPA=11|draw_SPA=7|loss_SPA=12|gf_SPA=43|ga_SPA=44\n|win_MOS=10|draw_MOS=10|loss_MOS=10|gf_MOS=38|ga_MOS=39\n|win_RUB=7|draw_RUB=12|loss_RUB=11|gf_RUB=32|ga_RUB=31\n|win_AMK=6|draw_AMK=12|loss_AMK=12|gf_AMK=27|ga_AMK=42\n|win_ROS=7|draw_ROS=8|loss_ROS=15|gf_ROS=28|ga_ROS=42\n|win_DYN=6|draw_DYN=11|loss_DYN=13|gf_DYN=2